.TH JENNIFER-GO 1 "2026" "Jennifer" "Jennifer Programming Language"
.SH NAME
jennifer-go \- Jennifer programming language interpreter (standard Go build)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jennifer-go
.I subcommand
.RI [ args ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jennifer-go
is the standard-Go build of the Jennifer interpreter, shipped
alongside the canonical TinyGo build
.BR jennifer (1).
Same source code, same language; only the compiler differs. The
Go build is the performance variant: roughly two to five times
faster than
.B jennifer
on compute-bound workloads (recursion, tight numeric loops,
arithmetic) at the cost of a larger binary. Pick this one when the
script is computation-heavy and binary size doesn't matter.
.PP
The language surface and the subcommand set are identical to
.BR jennifer (1) "; see that page for the full reference."
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR jennifer (1),
.UR https://github.com/mplx/jennifer-lang
.UE
